{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I'm going to talk to you about you about the political chemistry of oil spills"},{"time":3000,"text":"and why this is an incredibly important,"},{"time":6000,"text":"long, oily, hot summer,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and why we need to keep ourselves from getting distracted."},{"time":11000,"text":"But before I talk about the political chemistry,"},{"time":13000,"text":"I actually need to talk about the chemistry of oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16000,"text":"This is a photograph from when I visited"},{"time":18000,"text":"Prudhoe Bay in Alaska in 2002"},{"time":21000,"text":"to watch the Minerals Management Service"},{"time":23000,"text":"testing their ability"},{"time":25000,"text":"to burn oil spills in ice."},{"time":27000,"text":"And what you see here is, you see a little bit of crude oil,"},{"time":29000,"text":"you see some ice cubes,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and you see two sandwich baggies of napalm."},{"time":34000,"text":"The napalm is burning there quite nicely."},{"time":36000,"text":"And the thing is, is that"},{"time":38000,"text":"oil is really an abstraction for us as the American consumer."},{"time":41000,"text":"We're four percent of the world's population;"},{"time":43000,"text":"we use 25 percent of the world's oil production."},{"time":46000,"text":"And we don't really understand what oil is,"},{"time":49000,"text":"until you check out its molecules,"},{"time":51000,"text":"And you don't really understand that until you see this stuff burn."},{"time":54000,"text":"So this is what happens as that burn gets going."},{"time":56000,"text":"It takes off. It's a big woosh."},{"time":58000,"text":"I highly recommend that you get a chance to see crude oil burn someday,"},{"time":61000,"text":"because you will never need to hear another poli sci lecture"},{"time":64000,"text":"on the geopolitics of oil again."},{"time":67000,"text":"It'll just bake your retinas."},{"time":69000,"text":"So there it is; the retinas are baking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"Let me tell you a little bit about this chemistry of oil."},{"time":74000,"text":"Oil is a stew of hydrocarbon molecules."},{"time":77000,"text":"It starts of with the very small ones,"},{"time":79000,"text":"which are one carbon, four hydrogen --"},{"time":81000,"text":"that's methane -- it just floats off."},{"time":83000,"text":"Then there's all sorts of intermediate ones with middle amounts of carbon."},{"time":86000,"text":"You've probably heard of benzene rings; they're very carcinogenic."},{"time":89000,"text":"And it goes all the way over"},{"time":91000,"text":"to these big, thick, galumphy ones that have hundreds of carbons,"},{"time":93000,"text":"and they have thousands of hydrogens,"},{"time":95000,"text":"and they have vanadium and heavy metals and sulfur"},{"time":97000,"text":"and all kinds of craziness hanging off the sides of them."},{"time":99000,"text":"Those are called the asphaltenes; they're an ingredient in asphalt."},{"time":102000,"text":"They're very important in oil spills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"Let me tell you a little bit about"},{"time":106000,"text":"the chemistry of oil in water."},{"time":109000,"text":"It is this chemistry that makes oil so disastrous."},{"time":112000,"text":"Oil doesn't sink, it floats."},{"time":114000,"text":"If it sank, it would be a whole different story as far as an oil spill."},{"time":117000,"text":"And the other thing it does is it spreads out the moment it hits the water."},{"time":120000,"text":"It spreads out to be really thin,"},{"time":122000,"text":"so you have a hard time corralling it."},{"time":124000,"text":"The next thing that happens"},{"time":126000,"text":"is the light ends evaporate,"},{"time":129000,"text":"and some of the toxic things float into the water column"},{"time":132000,"text":"and kill fish eggs"},{"time":134000,"text":"and smaller fish and things like that, and shrimp."},{"time":137000,"text":"And then the asphaltenes -- and this is the crucial thing --"},{"time":139000,"text":"the asphaltenes get whipped by the waves"},{"time":142000,"text":"into a frothy emulsion, something like mayonnaise."},{"time":144000,"text":"It triples the amount"},{"time":146000,"text":"of oily, messy goo that you have in the water,"},{"time":149000,"text":"and it makes it very hard to handle."},{"time":151000,"text":"It also makes it very viscous."},{"time":153000,"text":"When the Prestige sank off the coast of Spain,"},{"time":156000,"text":"there were big, floating cushions the size of sofa cushions"},{"time":159000,"text":"of emulsified oil,"},{"time":161000,"text":"with the consistency, or the viscosity, of chewing gum."},{"time":163000,"text":"It's incredibly hard to clean up."},{"time":165000,"text":"And every single oil is different when it hits water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168000,"text":"When the chemistry of the oil and water"},{"time":170000,"text":"also hits our politics,"},{"time":172000,"text":"it's absolutely explosive."},{"time":174000,"text":"For the first time, American consumers"},{"time":176000,"text":"will kind of see the oil supply chain in front of themselves."},{"time":180000,"text":"They have a \"eureka!\" moment,"},{"time":182000,"text":"when we suddenly understand oil in a different context."},{"time":185000,"text":"So I'm going to talk just a little bit about the origin of these politics,"},{"time":188000,"text":"because it's really crucial to understanding"},{"time":190000,"text":"why this summer is so important, why we need to stay focused."},{"time":193000,"text":"Nobody gets up in the morning and thinks,"},{"time":195000,"text":"\"Wow! I'm going to go buy"},{"time":197000,"text":"some three-carbon-to-12-carbon molecules to put in my tank"},{"time":199000,"text":"and drive happily to work.\""},{"time":201000,"text":"No, they think, \"Ugh. I have to go buy gas."},{"time":203000,"text":"I'm so angry about it. The oil companies are ripping me off."},{"time":205000,"text":"They set the prices, and I don't even know."},{"time":207000,"text":"I am helpless over this.\""},{"time":209000,"text":"And this is what happens to us at the gas pump --"},{"time":211000,"text":"and actually, gas pumps are specifically designed"},{"time":213000,"text":"to diffuse that anger."},{"time":215000,"text":"You might notice that many gas pumps, including this one,"},{"time":217000,"text":"are designed to look like ATMs."},{"time":219000,"text":"I've talked to engineers. That's specifically to diffuse our anger,"},{"time":222000,"text":"because supposedly we feel good about ATMs."},{"time":224000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":226000,"text":"That shows you how bad it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"But actually, I mean, this feeling of helplessness"},{"time":230000,"text":"comes in because most Americans actually feel"},{"time":233000,"text":"that oil prices are the result of a conspiracy,"},{"time":236000,"text":"not of the vicissitudes of the world oil market."},{"time":239000,"text":"And the thing is, too,"},{"time":241000,"text":"is that we also feel very helpless about the amount that we consume,"},{"time":243000,"text":"which is somewhat reasonable,"},{"time":245000,"text":"because in fact, we have designed this system"},{"time":248000,"text":"where, if you want to get a job,"},{"time":251000,"text":"it's much more important to have a car that runs,"},{"time":254000,"text":"to have a job and keep a job, than to have a GED."},{"time":257000,"text":"And that's actually very perverse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"Now there's another perverse thing about the way we buy gas,"},{"time":261000,"text":"which is that we'd rather be doing anything else."},{"time":263000,"text":"This is BP's gas station"},{"time":265000,"text":"in downtown Los Angeles."},{"time":267000,"text":"It is green. It is a shrine to greenishness."},{"time":270000,"text":"\"Now,\" you think, \"why would something so lame"},{"time":273000,"text":"work on people so smart?\""},{"time":275000,"text":"Well, the reason is, is because, when we're buying gas,"},{"time":278000,"text":"we're very invested in this sort of cognitive dissonance."},{"time":281000,"text":"I mean, we're angry at the one hand and we want to be somewhere else."},{"time":284000,"text":"We don't want to be buying oil;"},{"time":286000,"text":"we want to be doing something green."},{"time":288000,"text":"And we get kind of in on our own con."},{"time":291000,"text":"I mean -- and this is funny,"},{"time":293000,"text":"it looks funny here."},{"time":295000,"text":"But in fact, that's why the slogan \"beyond petroleum\" worked."},{"time":298000,"text":"But it's an inherent part of our energy policy,"},{"time":301000,"text":"which is we don't talk about"},{"time":303000,"text":"reducing the amount of oil that we use."},{"time":305000,"text":"We talk about energy independence. We talk about hydrogen cars."},{"time":308000,"text":"We talk about biofuels that haven't been invented yet."},{"time":310000,"text":"And so, cognitive dissonance"},{"time":313000,"text":"is part and parcel of the way that we deal with oil,"},{"time":316000,"text":"and it's really important to dealing with this oil spill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"Okay, so the politics of oil"},{"time":321000,"text":"are very moral in the United States."},{"time":323000,"text":"The oil industry is like a huge, gigantic octopus"},{"time":326000,"text":"of engineering and finance"},{"time":328000,"text":"and everything else,"},{"time":330000,"text":"but we actually see it in very moral terms."},{"time":332000,"text":"This is an early-on photograph -- you can see, we had these gushers."},{"time":335000,"text":"Early journalists looked at these spills,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and they said, \"This is a filthy industry.\""},{"time":339000,"text":"But they also saw in it"},{"time":341000,"text":"that people were getting rich for doing nothing."},{"time":343000,"text":"They weren't farmers, they were just getting rich for stuff coming out of the ground."},{"time":346000,"text":"It's the \"Beverly Hillbillies,\" basically."},{"time":348000,"text":"But in the beginning, this was seen as a very morally problematic thing,"},{"time":351000,"text":"long before it became funny."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"And then, of course, there was John D. Rockefeller."},{"time":356000,"text":"And the thing about John D. is that"},{"time":358000,"text":"he went into this chaotic wild-east"},{"time":360000,"text":"of oil industry,"},{"time":362000,"text":"and he rationalized it"},{"time":364000,"text":"into a vertically integrated company, a multinational."},{"time":367000,"text":"It was terrifying; you think Walmart is a terrifying business model now,"},{"time":370000,"text":"imagine what this looked like in the 1860s or 1870s."},{"time":373000,"text":"And it also the kind of root"},{"time":376000,"text":"of how we see oil as a conspiracy."},{"time":379000,"text":"But what's really amazing is that"},{"time":381000,"text":"Ida Tarbell, the journalist,"},{"time":384000,"text":"went in and did a big exposé of Rockefeller"},{"time":387000,"text":"and actually got the whole antitrust laws"},{"time":389000,"text":"put in place."},{"time":391000,"text":"But in many ways,"},{"time":393000,"text":"that image of the conspiracy still sticks with us."},{"time":395000,"text":"And here's one of the things"},{"time":397000,"text":"that Ida Tarbell said --"},{"time":399000,"text":"she said, \"He has a thin nose like a thorn."},{"time":402000,"text":"There were no lips."},{"time":404000,"text":"There were puffs under the little colorless eyes"},{"time":406000,"text":"with creases running from them.\""},{"time":408000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":410000,"text":"Okay, so that guy is actually still with us."},{"time":412000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":414000,"text":"I mean, this is a very pervasive -- this is part of our DNA."},{"time":417000,"text":"And then there's this guy, okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"So, you might be wondering why it is that,"},{"time":422000,"text":"every time we have high oil prices or an oil spill,"},{"time":424000,"text":"we call these CEOs down to Washington,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and we sort of pepper them with questions in public and we try to shame them."},{"time":430000,"text":"And this is something that we've been doing since 1974,"},{"time":433000,"text":"when we first asked them, \"Why are there these obscene profits?\""},{"time":436000,"text":"And we've sort of personalized the whole oil industry"},{"time":438000,"text":"into these CEOs."},{"time":440000,"text":"And we take it as, you know --"},{"time":443000,"text":"we look at it on a moral level,"},{"time":445000,"text":"rather than looking at it on a legal and financial level."},{"time":448000,"text":"And so I'm not saying these guys aren't liable to answer questions --"},{"time":451000,"text":"I'm just saying that, when you focus on"},{"time":453000,"text":"whether they are or are not a bunch of greedy bastards,"},{"time":456000,"text":"you don't actually get around to the point"},{"time":458000,"text":"of making laws that are either going to either change the way they operate,"},{"time":461000,"text":"or you're going to get around"},{"time":463000,"text":"to really reducing the amount of oil"},{"time":465000,"text":"and reducing our dependence on oil."},{"time":467000,"text":"So I'm saying this is kind of a distraction."},{"time":469000,"text":"But it makes for good theater,"},{"time":471000,"text":"and it's powerfully cathartic as you probably saw last week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"So the thing about water oil spills"},{"time":477000,"text":"is that they are very politically galvanizing."},{"time":480000,"text":"I mean, these pictures -- this is from the Santa Barbara spill."},{"time":483000,"text":"You have these pictures of birds."},{"time":485000,"text":"They really influence people."},{"time":487000,"text":"When the Santa Barbara spill happened in 1969,"},{"time":490000,"text":"it formed the environmental movement in its modern form."},{"time":492000,"text":"It started Earth Day."},{"time":494000,"text":"It also put in place the National Environmental Policy Act,"},{"time":497000,"text":"the Clean Air Act, the Clean Water Act."},{"time":500000,"text":"Everything that we are really stemmed from this period."},{"time":503000,"text":"I think it's important to kind of look at these pictures of the birds"},{"time":506000,"text":"and understand what happens to us."},{"time":508000,"text":"Here we are normally;"},{"time":510000,"text":"we're standing at the gas pump, and we're feeling kind of helpless."},{"time":512000,"text":"We look at these pictures"},{"time":514000,"text":"and we understand, for the first time, our role in this supply chain."},{"time":517000,"text":"We connect the dots in the supply chain."},{"time":519000,"text":"And we have this kind of --"},{"time":521000,"text":"as voters, we have kind of a \"eureka!\" moment."},{"time":524000,"text":"This is why these moments of these oil spills"},{"time":526000,"text":"are so important."},{"time":528000,"text":"But it's also really important that we don't get distracted"},{"time":531000,"text":"by the theater or the morals of it."},{"time":533000,"text":"We actually need to go in"},{"time":535000,"text":"and work on the roots of the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537000,"text":"One of the things that happened with the two previous oil spills"},{"time":540000,"text":"was that we really worked on some of the symptoms."},{"time":543000,"text":"We were very reactive, as opposed to being proactive"},{"time":545000,"text":"about what happened."},{"time":547000,"text":"And so what we did was, actually,"},{"time":549000,"text":"we made moratoriums on the east and west coasts on drilling."},{"time":552000,"text":"We stopped drilling in ANWR,"},{"time":555000,"text":"but we didn't actually reduce the amount of oil that we consumed."},{"time":558000,"text":"In fact, it's continued to increase."},{"time":560000,"text":"The only thing that really reduces the amount of oil that we consume"},{"time":563000,"text":"is much higher prices."},{"time":565000,"text":"As you can see, our own production has fallen off"},{"time":567000,"text":"as our reservoirs have gotten old and expensive to drill out."},{"time":569000,"text":"We only have two percent of the world's oil reserves;"},{"time":572000,"text":"65 percent of them are in the Persian Gulf."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"One of the things that's happened because of this"},{"time":577000,"text":"is that, since 1969,"},{"time":580000,"text":"the country of Nigeria, or the part of Nigeria that pumps oil,"},{"time":583000,"text":"which is the delta -- which is two times the size of Maryland --"},{"time":586000,"text":"has had thousands of oil spills a year."},{"time":588000,"text":"I mean, we've essentially been exporting oil spills"},{"time":590000,"text":"when we import oil from places"},{"time":592000,"text":"without tight environmental regulations."},{"time":594000,"text":"That has been the equivalent of an Exxon Valdez spill"},{"time":597000,"text":"every year since 1969."},{"time":600000,"text":"And we can wrap our heads around the spills,"},{"time":602000,"text":"because that's what we see here,"},{"time":604000,"text":"but in fact, these guys actually live in a war zone."},{"time":606000,"text":"There's a thousand battle-related deaths a year"},{"time":609000,"text":"in this area twice the size of Maryland,"},{"time":611000,"text":"and it's all related to the oil."},{"time":613000,"text":"And these guys, I mean, if they were in the U.S.,"},{"time":615000,"text":"they might be actually here in this room."},{"time":617000,"text":"They have degrees in political science, degrees in business --"},{"time":619000,"text":"they're entrepreneurs. They don't actually want to be doing what they're doing."},{"time":623000,"text":"And it's sort of one of the other groups of people"},{"time":626000,"text":"who pay a price for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"The other thing that we've done,"},{"time":630000,"text":"as we've continued to increase demand,"},{"time":632000,"text":"is that we kind of play a shell game with the costs."},{"time":635000,"text":"One of the places we put in a big oil project"},{"time":638000,"text":"in Chad, with Exxon."},{"time":640000,"text":"So the U.S. taxpayer paid for it;"},{"time":642000,"text":"the World Bank, Exxon paid for it."},{"time":644000,"text":"We put it in. There was a tremendous banditry problem."},{"time":647000,"text":"I was there in 2003."},{"time":649000,"text":"We were driving along this dark, dark road,"},{"time":651000,"text":"and the guy in the green stepped out,"},{"time":653000,"text":"and I was just like, \"Ahhh! This is it.\""},{"time":656000,"text":"And then the guy in the Exxon uniform stepped out,"},{"time":659000,"text":"and we realized it was okay."},{"time":661000,"text":"They have their own private sort of army around them at the oil fields."},{"time":663000,"text":"But at the same time,"},{"time":665000,"text":"Chad has become much more unstable,"},{"time":667000,"text":"and we are not paying for that price at the pump."},{"time":670000,"text":"We pay for it in our taxes on April 15th."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"We do the same thing"},{"time":675000,"text":"with the price of policing the Persian Gulf"},{"time":677000,"text":"and keeping the shipping lanes open."},{"time":679000,"text":"This is 1988 --"},{"time":681000,"text":"we actually bombed two Iranian oil platforms that year."},{"time":684000,"text":"That was the beginning of an escalating U.S. involvement there"},{"time":686000,"text":"that we do not pay for at the pump."},{"time":688000,"text":"We pay for it on April 15th,"},{"time":690000,"text":"and we can't even calculate the cost of this involvement."},{"time":693000,"text":"The other place that is sort of supporting our dependence on oil"},{"time":696000,"text":"and our increased consumption"},{"time":699000,"text":"is the Gulf of Mexico,"},{"time":701000,"text":"which was not part of the moratoriums."},{"time":703000,"text":"Now what's happened in the Gulf of Mexico -- as you can see,"},{"time":705000,"text":"this is the Minerals Management diagram"},{"time":707000,"text":"of wells for gas and oil."},{"time":709000,"text":"It's become this intense industrialized zone."},{"time":711000,"text":"It doesn't have the same resonance for us"},{"time":713000,"text":"that the Arctic National Wildlife Refuge has,"},{"time":715000,"text":"but it should, I mean, it's a bird sanctuary."},{"time":718000,"text":"Also, every time you buy gasoline in the United States,"},{"time":720000,"text":"half of it is actually being refined along the coast,"},{"time":723000,"text":"because the Gulf actually has"},{"time":725000,"text":"about 50 percent of our refining capacity"},{"time":727000,"text":"and a lot of our marine terminals as well."},{"time":729000,"text":"So the people of the Gulf have essentially been subsidizing the rest of us"},{"time":732000,"text":"through a less-clean environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735000,"text":"And finally, American families also pay a price for oil."},{"time":738000,"text":"Now on the one hand, the price at the pump is not really very high"},{"time":741000,"text":"when you consider the actual cost of the oil,"},{"time":743000,"text":"but on the other hand,"},{"time":745000,"text":"the fact that people have no other transit options"},{"time":748000,"text":"means that they pay a large amount of their income"},{"time":751000,"text":"into just getting back and forth to work,"},{"time":753000,"text":"generally in a fairly crummy car."},{"time":755000,"text":"If you look at people who make $50,000 a year, they have two kids,"},{"time":758000,"text":"they might have three jobs or more,"},{"time":760000,"text":"and then they have to really commute."},{"time":762000,"text":"They're actually spending more on their car and fuel"},{"time":765000,"text":"than they are on taxes or on health care."},{"time":767000,"text":"And the same thing happens"},{"time":769000,"text":"at the 50th percentile, around 80,000."},{"time":772000,"text":"Gasoline costs are a tremendous drain"},{"time":774000,"text":"on the American economy,"},{"time":776000,"text":"but they're also a drain on individual families"},{"time":779000,"text":"and it's kind of terrifying to think about what happens when prices get higher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782000,"text":"So, what I'm going to talk to you about now is:"},{"time":785000,"text":"what do we have to do this time?"},{"time":787000,"text":"What are the laws? What do we have to do to keep ourselves focused?"},{"time":790000,"text":"One thing is -- we need to stay away from the theater."},{"time":792000,"text":"We need to stay away from the moratoriums."},{"time":794000,"text":"We need to focus really back again"},{"time":796000,"text":"on the molecules."},{"time":798000,"text":"The moratoriums are fine, but we do need to focus"},{"time":801000,"text":"on the molecules on the oil."},{"time":803000,"text":"One of the things that we also need to do,"},{"time":805000,"text":"is we need to try to not kind of fool ourselves"},{"time":807000,"text":"into thinking that you can have a green world,"},{"time":810000,"text":"before you reduce the amount of oil that we use."},{"time":812000,"text":"We need to focus on reducing the oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"What you see in this top drawing is a schematic"},{"time":817000,"text":"of how petroleum gets used in the U.S. economy."},{"time":819000,"text":"It comes in on the side -- the useful stuff is the dark gray,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and the un-useful stuff,"},{"time":824000,"text":"which is called the rejected energy -- the waste,"},{"time":827000,"text":"goes up to the top."},{"time":829000,"text":"Now you can see that the waste far outweighs"},{"time":831000,"text":"the actually useful amount."},{"time":833000,"text":"And one of the things that we need to do"},{"time":835000,"text":"is, not only fix the fuel efficiency of our vehicles"},{"time":837000,"text":"and make them much more efficient,"},{"time":839000,"text":"but we also need to fix the economy in general."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"We need to remove the perverse incentives to use more fuel."},{"time":844000,"text":"For example, we have an insurance system"},{"time":846000,"text":"where the person who drives 20,000 miles a year"},{"time":849000,"text":"pays the same insurance as somebody who drives 3,000."},{"time":852000,"text":"We actually encourage people to drive more."},{"time":854000,"text":"We have policies that reward sprawl -- we have all kinds of policies."},{"time":857000,"text":"We need to have more mobility choices."},{"time":859000,"text":"We need to make the gas price"},{"time":861000,"text":"better reflect the real cost of oil."},{"time":863000,"text":"And we need to shift subsidies from the oil industry,"},{"time":866000,"text":"which is at least 10 billion dollars a year,"},{"time":869000,"text":"into something that allows middle-class people to find better ways to commute."},{"time":872000,"text":"Whether that's getting a much more efficient car"},{"time":875000,"text":"and also kind of building markets"},{"time":877000,"text":"for new cars and new fuels down the road,"},{"time":879000,"text":"this is where we need to be."},{"time":881000,"text":"We need to kind of rationalize this whole thing,"},{"time":883000,"text":"and you can find more about this policy."},{"time":885000,"text":"It's called STRONG, which is \"Secure Transportation"},{"time":887000,"text":"Reducing Oil Needs Gradually,\""},{"time":889000,"text":"and the idea is instead of being helpless, we need to be more strong."},{"time":892000,"text":"They're up at NewAmerica.net."},{"time":894000,"text":"What's important about these"},{"time":896000,"text":"is that we try to move"},{"time":898000,"text":"from feeling helpless at the pump,"},{"time":900000,"text":"to actually being active"},{"time":902000,"text":"and to really sort of thinking about who we are,"},{"time":905000,"text":"having kind of that special moment,"},{"time":907000,"text":"where we connect the dots actually at the pump."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910000,"text":"Now supposedly, oil taxes"},{"time":913000,"text":"are the third rail of American politics -- the no-fly zone."},{"time":916000,"text":"I actually -- I agree that a dollar a gallon on oil"},{"time":918000,"text":"is probably too much,"},{"time":920000,"text":"but I think that if we started this year"},{"time":922000,"text":"with three cents a gallon on gasoline,"},{"time":925000,"text":"and upped it to six cents next year, nine cents the following year,"},{"time":928000,"text":"all the way up to 30 cents by 2020,"},{"time":931000,"text":"that we could actually significantly reduce our gasoline consumption,"},{"time":934000,"text":"and at the same time we would give people time to prepare,"},{"time":937000,"text":"time to respond,"},{"time":939000,"text":"and we would be raising money and raising consciousness at the same time."},{"time":942000,"text":"Let me give you a little sense of how this would work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":945000,"text":"This is a gas receipt, hypothetically, for a year from now."},{"time":948000,"text":"The first thing that you have on the tax is --"},{"time":950000,"text":"you have a tax for a stronger America -- 33 cents."},{"time":953000,"text":"So you're not helpless at the pump."},{"time":955000,"text":"And the second thing that you have is a kind of warning sign,"},{"time":958000,"text":"very similar to what you would find"},{"time":960000,"text":"on a cigarette pack."},{"time":962000,"text":"And what it says is, \"The National Academy of Sciences"},{"time":965000,"text":"estimates that every gallon of gas you burn in your car"},{"time":968000,"text":"creates 29 cents in health care costs.\""},{"time":970000,"text":"That's a lot."},{"time":972000,"text":"And so this -- you can see that you're paying considerably less"},{"time":974000,"text":"than the health care costs on the tax."},{"time":977000,"text":"And also, the hope is that"},{"time":980000,"text":"you start to be connected to the whole greater system."},{"time":983000,"text":"And at the same time, you have a number that you can call"},{"time":985000,"text":"to get more information on commuting,"},{"time":988000,"text":"or a low-interest loan on a different kind of car,"},{"time":991000,"text":"or whatever it is you're going to need"},{"time":993000,"text":"to actually reduce your gasoline dependence."},{"time":997000,"text":"With this whole sort of suite of policies,"},{"time":999000,"text":"we could actually reduce our gasoline consumption --"},{"time":1001000,"text":"or our oil consumption --"},{"time":1003000,"text":"by 20 percent by 2020."},{"time":1006000,"text":"So, three million barrels a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009000,"text":"But in order to do this,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"one of the things we really need to do, is we need to remember"},{"time":1013000,"text":"we are people of the hydrocarbon."},{"time":1015000,"text":"We need to keep or minds on the molecules"},{"time":1017000,"text":"and not get distracted by the theater,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"not get distracted by the cognitive dissonance"},{"time":1022000,"text":"of the green possibilities that are out there."},{"time":1024000,"text":"We need to kind of get down and do the gritty work"},{"time":1026000,"text":"of reducing our dependence upon this fuel and these molecules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}